<br>
Ranting about game issues is one thing - bugs, gameplay problems, that loser that trained you last night...<br>
<br>
... but flaming I have always found to be something else entirely.  People say things like &quot;I speak openly&quot; or &quot;In my guild we say it like it is&quot; or &quot;Let's call a spade a spade...&quot; but are really just too fired up and/or immature to make a constructive post.  Everyone jumps into these burning houses and the topic does a downward spiral - often creating lasting rifts between people that could otherwise have gotten along just fine.<br>
<br>
Flames have no class whatsoever.  If people have a problem with someone/something or the guild itself, they should handle it in /tell where possible, or make constructive posts that offer explanations of the issue and possible solutions.<br>
<br>
No pointing fingers, no name calling... if you really hate someone - send them a tell, the rest of us don't need to read it. <p><p align="center"><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Mullzy &lt;Infinitus Vindicat&gt; ~
